Kovalchuk’s Media Group and RTL May Swap Assets, Kommersant Says

-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 
2011-05-20T04:39:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-20/kovalchuk-s-media-group-and-rtl-may-swap-assets-kommersant-says.html
National Media Group, controlled by
Russian billionaire Yury Kovalchuk, and Luxembourg-based RTL
Group are close to completing an asset-swap transaction,
 Kommersant  reported, citing an unidentified person familiar with
the matter.  National Media may get 30 percent of  Russia ’s REN TV,
making it the channel’s sole owner; RTL may get 7.5 percent of
National Media’s shares and a place on its board, the newspaper
said. An RTL representative declined to comment and National
Media’s general director, Alexander Ordzhonikidze, neither
confirmed nor denied the information about the transaction,
Kommersant said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marina Sysoyeva in Moscow 
 msysoyeva@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
